  "text": "The results of the univariate regression analyses performed for FAZ area and each variable are displayed in Table 3 . CRT and retinal vascular density were each found to be negatively correlated with FAZ area (CRT: P < 0.001, R 2 = 0.356; retinal vascular density: P < 0.001, R 2 = 0.189; Fig 2A and 2B) . We found no significant correlation between age and FAZ area (P = 0.261, R 2 = 0.188, Fig   2C) . Because a previous study reported that FAZ area expands significantly after the age of 40 [CITATION_1] , we conducted another examination using the age of 40 as a cutoff point. Among subjects younger than 40, age was not significantly correlated with FAZ area (P = 0.312, R 2 = 0.178, Fig   2D) . However, among subjects aged 40 years or older, age was positively correlated with FAZ area (P = 0.001, R 2 = 0.258, Fig 2D) .",
